        "client_msg_id": "bde23687-4843-4339-9ba4-e1dd5763bcd4",
        "text": "So you mean that part?:\n```$(XTRA_LIB):\n\tmkdir crc32c\/build &amp;&amp; \\\n\t\tcd crc32c\/build &amp;&amp; \\\n\t\t${CMAKE} .. &amp;&amp; \\\n\t\t${MAKE} all &amp;&amp; \\\n\t\tcp -v libcrc32c.a .. &amp;&amp; \\\n\t\trm -rf *```\nTechnically it’s inside src but I get the idea it can be anywhere and is the external source code.\nSo it’s not R CMD which drives the process but CMAKE?",
        "team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "user_team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "source_team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "f7ccd27ca9d6",
