        "client_msg_id": "2d167053-c473-4ddf-9cf2-34bcd89bd7d0",
        "text": "Both as `R CMD INSTALL` will invoke `cmake` for you. Here `cmake` is a given (as that is how the upstream is packaged).  _Where you place those sources_ is up to you, you can also put them into `external\/src\/whereever` and you then adjust the path to the static library in `src\/Makevars`.\n\nIt is all under your control.  When I work these things out I often create test packages, sometimes using both approach.  You could even create a 'fake library', say `doubler` that just doubles an `int` or `double` in two helper functions and then go through the motions of packaging it.\n\nThe good news is that there are a TON of examples out there.",
        "team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "user_team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "source_team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "user_profile": {
